      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CRENSHAW KING (1) settled down midfield and held his position to the line when finishing 5th (17.82) at Northam. Form here at the trip sound including three wins. Has performed well from this box with a win and two minor placings to his name from five starts. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. TURBO TATE (2) turned in a good run last time, finishing in the placings (22.96) at this track in a Grade 5. Lines up from box 2 for the first time. Solid record at the distance winning four races. Expecting another good run. MERL'S LAD (3) hit the frame after colliding with another runner last time in a Grade 5/6 at this track, finishing a 2.5 lengths third (22.79). This tougher but looks a leading chance again. RACCOON RIVER (7) placed last time and cannot be ignored.",
